Single carrier.Clinical History:
Proband, Baby of Ashwini is a second-born female child to a third-degree consanguineous couple. She
presented with chief complaints of elevated serum ammonia and lactate levels at 1 day of life. Newborn
screening revealed normal parameters for amnio acid profiles and acylcarnitine profiles. During the
antenatal period Clinical exome sequencing [AND23590020933] was performed in the amniotic fluid
which revealed the fetus was homozygous for a likely pathogenic variant C11orf80: c.285dupT causative
of Hydatidiform mole recurrent, 4. Additionally, the fetus was also heterozygous for 2 likely pathogenic
variants SLC25A20: c.496C>T causative of Carnitine-acylcarnitine translocase deficiency and DNAH8:
c.12967delA causative of Spermatogenic failure 46 and one variant of uncertain significance RYR1:
c.14707G>A causative of {Malignant hyperthermia susceptibility 1}, Congenital myopathy 1A, autosomal
dominant, with susceptibility to malignant hyperthermia, King-Denborough syndrome, Congenital
myopathy 1B, autosomal recessive. Her elder brother was delivered full-term via LSCS and cried
immediately after birth. He presented with lethargy, apnea, respiratory alkalosis, and hypoglycemia. His
serum ammonia and lactate levels were elevated. New-born Screening test revealed abnormal
parameters of organic acid/fatty acids and increased levels of palmitoyl carnitine and low levels of free
carnitine. He succumbed at 5 days of life. Carrier Screening by Clinical exome sequencing
(AND23590017617 & AND23590017616) in both the parents revealed they are heterozygous carrier for
two likely pathogenic variants SLC25A20: c.496C>T causative of Carnitine acylcarnitine translocase
deficiency and C11orf80: c.285dupT causative of Hydatidiform mole, recurrent, 4. Additionally, male
partner was found to be heterozygous for two likely pathogenic variants DNAH8: c.12967delA causative
of Spermatogenic failure 46 and DNAI1: c.1703G>A causative of Ciliary dyskinesia, primary, 1, with or
without situs inversus and one variant of uncertain significance RYR1: c.14707G>A causative of {Malignant
hyperthermia susceptibility 1}, Congenital myopathy 1A, autosomal dominant, with susceptibility to
malignant hyperthermia, King-Denborough syndrome, Congenital myopathy 1B, autosomal recessive and
the female partner is heterozygous for one variant of uncertain significance COL4A4: c.4496A>C causative
of Alport syndrome 2, autosomal recessive, Hematuria, familial benign, 1. Mrs. Ashwini's brother
succumbed to renal failure at 19 years of age. Proband, Baby of Ashwini has been evaluated for pathogenic
variations.
